printer_notes.3.0.0: Do not remove the following keywords! These keywords are used in the "compatible printer" condition of the print and filament profiles to link the particular print and filament profiles to this printer profile.\nPRINTER_VENDOR_ELEGOO\nPRINTER_MODEL_NEPTUNE2D

start_gcode.3.0.0:
T[initial_tool] ; set active extruder
M413 S0 ; disable Power Loss Recovery
G90 ; use absolute coordinates
M83 ; extruder relative mode
M140 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[0]} ; set final bed temp
M104 S150 ; set temporary nozzle temp to prevent oozing during homing and auto bed leveling
G4 S10 ; allow partial nozzle warmup
G28 ; home all axis
;G29 ; auto bed levelling - remove ; at beginning of line to enable
;M420 S1 ; enable mesh - remove ; at beginning of line to enable
G1 Z50 F240
G1 X2 Y10 F3000
M104 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} ; set final nozzle temp
M190 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[0]} ; wait for bed temp to stabilize
M109 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} ; wait for nozzle temp to stabilize
G1 Z0.28 F240 ; move down to prime nozzle
G92 E0 ; reset extruder
G1 E90 ; load filament
G92 E0 ; reset extruder
G1 Y140 E10 F1500 ; prime the nozzle
G1 X2.3 F5000 ; move over for second prime line
G92 E0 ; reset extruder
G1 Y10 E10 F1200 ; prime the nozzle
G92 E0 ; reset extruder
